otential importance of\nallowing for running in the slope and scatter of MPRs when modeling cluster\ncounts for cosmological studies. We tabulate LLR fit parameters as a function\nof halo mass at $z=0$, $0.5$ and 1 for two popular mass conventions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 Nov 2017 03:11:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-16"}
