ain positive for\nboth reactions, suggesting the dominance of $K^{*}$ exchange in the $t$\nchannel. These asymmetries increase gradually with the photon energy, and have\na maximum value of +0.6 for both reactions. Comparison with theoretical\npredictions based on the Regge trajectory in the $t$ channel and the\ncontributions of nucleon resonances indicates the major role of $t$-channel\ncontributions as well as non-negligible effects of nucleon resonances in\naccounting for the reaction mechanism of hyperon photoproduction in this photon\nenergy regime.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 Nov 2017 08:36:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 2 Feb 2018 02:41:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-05"}
